District-Wide, Albers And Bain (1985) Identified Three Main Linear Trends, N23?E, N37?E, And N60?E Defined By Faults, Clusters Of Ore Bodies And The Long Axes Of Ore Bodies.  Furthermore They Noted That Most Of The Large Ore Bodies Occur At The Intersections Of These Trends And Surmised That The Faults, Especially At The Intersections, Provided Conduits For Emanating Ore Fluids. Post-Mineral Normal Faults Disrupt The Lateral Continuity Of The Ore.   \N\Nthe Massive Sulfide Occurs With Sharp Contact Within The Upper Unit Of The Balaklala Rhyolite.
